messages.user_message: What is the appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite?
messages.assistant_response:
Based on the retrieved documents, the appropriate nozzle temperature for 3D printing PLA-Akermanite composites using fused deposition modeling (FDM) is **210°C**. This temperature was used for printing composite scaffolds with 70% porosity, a nozzle diameter of 400 μm, and a layer thickness of 400 μm at a printing speed of 10 mm/s [reference_117.pdf, page_label: 2]. 

Another document also mentions using a 3D printer (Prusa i3 MK3) for PLA-Akermanite composites but does not specify the exact nozzle temperature [reference_108.pdf, page_label: 14542]. 

For this specific case, the documented temperature is **210°C**.

messages.user_message: What is the appropriate printing speed for 3D printing using fused deposition modeling with polylactic acid (PLA) mixed with Akermanite?
messages.assistant_response:
The appropriate printing speed for 3D printing PLA-Akermanite composites using fused deposition modeling (FDM) is **10 mm/s**. This speed was used with a nozzle temperature of 210°C, a nozzle diameter of 400 μm, and a layer thickness of 400 μm to fabricate scaffolds with 70% porosity [reference_117.pdf, page_label: 2].  

No other printing speeds for PLA-Akermanite composites were mentioned in the retrieved documents.
